  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nAccording to http://truffleframework.com/docs/getting_started/testing#clean-room-environment, when running against Ethereum clients like Geth or Parity, Truffle should re-deploy all of a project's migrations at the beginning of every test file to ensure each test file starts with clean contract state. In practice, when running a test suite with multiple test files, I am not seeing state being reset via a re-deploy between test file runs when using Parity. The tests run fine with ganache-cli.\r\n\r\nThe project for reproducing is here: https://github.com/yondonfu/truffle-clean-room-repro. The contract is `contracts/Hello.sol` and the tests are in `test/integration`.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `docker pull livepeer/parity-dev`\r\n2. `docker run -d -p 8545:8545 --name parity-dev livepeer/parity-dev`\r\n3. `git clone http://github.com/yondonfu/truffle-clean-room-repro`\r\n4. `cd truffle-clean-room-repro`\r\n5. `truffle compile`\r\n6. `truffle test --network parity`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nAll tests should pass.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe test in `Hello2.js` fails. The test checks if `foo` is set to 0. If the contract was re-deployed and the test file started with clean contract state, `foo` should be 0. However, `foo` is instead 5 which is the value it was set to in `Hello1.js`\r\n\r\nIf I instead use Truffle's built-in development chain by running `truffle test`, all the tests pass.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSX\r\n* Truffle version: Truffle v4.0.1 (core: 4.0.1)\r\n* Ethereum client: Parity\r\n* node version: v8.5.0\r\n* npm version: 5.3.0",
